timeline.bodyText:
I would think the Kerberos service will do more than just get the config and keytab from the kerberos element. So we will know which keytab and config file that we use.
if (kerberos config)
get keytab and config files
else (get the default file name and location for keytab and config files)
We should print out the the kerberos config and keytab as an event.
The most common problem we see is which Kerberos config/keytab files that we use.

